						               													<description>Golems are beings created to fulfill tasks, but the meaning of those tasks depends on the principles of their creator. So if its creator loses its sanity, so will its golem... On your journey through the western wastes you come across one of these creatures guarding a corrupt and obviously dangerous portal. At his feet, his dead master several suns ago. His slave remains obedient fulfilling his insane legacy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solitaire mode expansion for Invocaci&amp;#195;&amp;#179;n Fronteras.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Includes 2 promo cards:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Yogzethot (54 - Earth/Fire)&amp;#10;     Incubo (26 - Air): A player discard 1 from their hand, you take 2 from the Portal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play in this 1-player mode, you only need a Summon deck and at least one board with which to correctly position the cards of the artificial opponent: the Golem.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to survive until the end of your 6 summons and get more points than the Golem. If the Golem manages to win 4 matches, the player loses the match and is defeated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
